Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of N-[(4-bromo- 3,5 - difluorine) phenyl]-acrylamide in methanol-ethanol solution
Citation.sAbstract: N-[(4-bromo-3,5-difluorine)phenyl]acrylamide is a new monomer for polyreaction. Its corresponding solid-liquilibrium data essential support for industrial design and further theoretical studies. Using a laser detecting system, solubility data were measured for title compound dissolved in different compositions of methanolethanol mixtures at the temperature range from 287.75 k to 339.55 k. The solubility data were correlated with Apelblat equation and Buchowski-Ksiazczak eh equation . The Buchowski-Ksiazczak eh equation can regress the solubility data much better than the Apelblat equation .
